Package: altparsers
Type: Package
Title: Use alternative parsers for R code
Version: 0.1
Date: 2012-11-02
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jim", "Hester", email = "james.f.hester@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Romain", "Francois", role = c("ctb"),
      comment = "parser package, from which this was adapted"),
    person("Andrew", "Redd", role = c("ctb"),
      comment = "parser package, from which this was adapted"),
    person("R Core team", role = "ctb",
      comment = "Original R parser code and supporting files")
    )
Description: Allows use of alternative parsers in R packages and interactively.
  These parsers generate regular R abstract syntax trees, but can contain
  additional features not present in the normal R parser.
License: GPL (>= 2.0)
Depends:
    R (>= 2.15.0),
    glue
Imports:
    utils,
    Rcpp (>= 0.9.11)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
LazyData: yes
URL: https://github.com/jimhester/altparsers
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
